The FAUNMAP Constituent Database

FAUNMAP is one of the original Neotoma Constituent Databases. FAUNMAP was originally developed by Russ Graham and Ernest Lundelius in the early 1990s with NSF funding. After they aggregated data from across the United States on mammalian occurrences for the past 50,000 years, the time frame it covered was extended to the past five million years.

FAUNMAP currently contains 6956 datasets from 4847 sites from the locations mapped below.
